Can see";s:20:"custom_edit_can_edit";s:8:"Can edit";s:21:"custom_edit_placement";s:16:"Choose Placement";s:30:"custom_edit_placement_standard";s:21:"Standard (with title)";s:31:"custom_edit_placement_withicons";s:10:"With Icons";s:36:"custom_edit_placement_abovesignature";s:15:"Above Signature";s:24:"custom_profile_placement";s:15:"Placement: %1$s";s:23:"custom_edit_delete_sure";s:80:"Are you sure you wish to delete this field - all related user data will be lost!";s:22:"standard_profile_title";s:23:"Standard Profile Fields";s:22:"standard_profile_field";s:5:"Field";s:24:"languages_area_edit_desc";s:204:"This area allows you to browse and edit the language data used by Wedge. It is not designed for translations, and if you wish to translate Wedge into a new language, please contact the Wedge Team instead.";s:19:"languages_lang_name";s:42:"Language Name (click to edit the language)";s:16:"languages_locale";s:6:"Locale";s:19:"languages_available";s:9:"Available";s:17:"languages_default";s:7:"Default";s:15:"languages_users";s:5:"Users";s:14:"edit_languages";s:14:"Edit Languages";s:23:"edit_languages_specific";s:21:"Edit Languages - %1$s";s:26:"language_edit_master_value";s:27:"<em>Master value:</em> %1$s";s:32:"language_edit_master_value_array";s:23:"<em>Master values:</em>";s:27:"language_edit_current_value";s:28:"<em>Current value:</em> %1$s";s:33:"language_edit_current_value_array";s:24:"<em>Current values:</em>";s:23:"language_edit_new_value";s:19:"<em>New value:</em>";s:29:"language_edit_new_value_array";s:20:"<em>New values:</em>";s:23:"language_edit_add_entry";s:12:"Add an entry";s:21:"language_delete_value";s:16:"Delete this item";s:21:"language_revert_value";s:21:"Reset to master value";s:20:"language_clear_cache";s:20:"Empty Language Cache";s:25:"language_clear_cache_desc";s:374:"The data used to make language items appear in the forum are managed between special files and the database, so that you can modify them without having to modify files. Generally you should use the language editor facilities from the administration area to change language items, but sometimes you may need to force the system to rebuild its cache. This allows you to do so.";s:24:"language_clear_cache_btn";s:15:"Clear the cache";s:22:"language_cache_cleared";s:36:"The language cache has been cleared.";s:19:"language_no_entries";s:137:"This particular language file has no entries, it is likely a placeholder and you really want the <a href="%1$s">parent language file</a>.";s:23:"language_search_results";s:21:"Search Results - %1$s";s:26:"language_no_result_results";s:37:"Unfortunately, no results were found.";s:23:"language_search_default";s:33:"Matches within the standard files";s:23:"language_search_plugins";s:22:"Matches within plugins";s:18:"language_edit_main";s:10:"Main Files";s:19:"language_edit_admin";s:11:"Admin Panel";s:21:"language_edit_default";s:22:"Default Language Files";s:19:"language_edit_other";s:20:"Other Language Files";s:20:"language_edit_search";s:21:"Search Language Files";s:28:"language_edit_search_plugins";s:16:"Include plugins?";s:25:"language_edit_search_keys";s:11:"Search keys";s:27:"language_edit_search_values";s:13:"Search values";s:25:"language_edit_search_both";s:11:"Search both";s:24:"language_edit_no_plugins";s:7:"Plugins";s:29:"language_edit_no_plugins_desc";s:53:"There are no editable language files for any plugins.";s:27:"language_edit_plugins_title";s:12:"Plugin: %1$s";s:23:"language_edit_elsewhere";s:20:"Configured elsewhere";s:29:"language_edit_email_templates";s:15:"Email templates";s:27:"language_edit_reg_agreement";s:22:"Registration agreement";s:21:"edit_language_entries";s:21:"Edit Language Entries";s:20:"languages_dictionary";s:10:"Dictionary";s:21:"languages_orientation";s:11:"Orientation";s:21:"languages_orients_ltr";s:13:"Left-to-Right";s:21:"languages_orients_rtl";s:13:"Right-to-Left";s:20:"lang_file_desc_index";s:39:"Main language file, all generic strings";s:21:"lang_file_desc_Modlog";s:22:"Moderation log entries";s:13:"homepage_desc";s:92:"This page allows you to determine what to show your users when they visit your forum\'s root.";s:13:"homepage_type";s:31:"What should the home page show?";s:18:"homepage_boardlist";s:10:"Board list";s:14:"homepage_board";s:14:"Specific board";s:15:"homepage_action";s:15:"Specific action";s:15:"homepage_custom";s:15:"Custom contents";s:20:"homepage_blurb_title";s:16:"Blurb title (%s)";s:14:"homepage_blurb";s:15:"Blurb text (%s)";s:16:"homepage_message";s:1041:"Choose "Board list" to show the full list of available boards; "Specific board" to direct users to a specific board in the list (make sure to
	choose which board, of course!); "Specific action" to direct them to a custom page on your forum (for instance, create files /app/Mine.php and /html/Mine.template.php,
	then enter "Mine" in the specific action box); and finally, "Custom contents" will allow you to show multiple elements at the same time. Enter one element per line
	(they\'ll be shown in order of appearance), from the following list:<br>

		<br><strong>blurb</strong>: a custom text; an introduction, maybe.
		<br><strong>topics</strong>: a list of the latest updated topics. Add \':x\' to start with x topics instead of 5, e.g. \'topics:10\'.
		<br><strong>thoughts</strong>: a list of the latest thoughts. Add \':x\' to show x thoughts instead of 10, e.g. \'thoughts:5\'.
		<br><strong>boards</strong>: the full list of boards.
		<br><strong>info</strong>: the information center (statistics). Desktop browsers show it in the sidebar.
